The paper deals with image stitching, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. The use of line features for geometric descriptions and scene constraints suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also deals with warping and optimization, which are common techniques in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of a global similarity constraint suggests that the paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category, as similarity transformations are commonly used in robot navigation. Finally, the use of optimization and constraints suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
